laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Ultrasound: Liver or Gallbladder US (Single Organ)
laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is mildly echogenic, which may reflect fatty deposition. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow. Common duct measures 4 mm. Gallbladder is tensely distended without mural edema or pericholecystic fluid. Two gallstones are seen measuring up to 1.7 cm, one may be impacted in the gallbladder neck.
